Enum Relation

  • java.lang.Object

    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<Relation>

    public enum Relation
extends java.lang.Enum<Relation>
    An enumeration of the possible directions to the relatives of a source.
    Since:
    0.2.0 ~2021.05.14
    Version:
    0.2.0
    Author:
    LSafer

        Previous (opposite)
        When the other source occurs before the source. 
             .....|--->.
     .<---|.....
     
        
     ......|-->.
     .<--|......

      • compute

        @Nullable
 @Contract(pure=true)
public static @Nullable Relation compute(int i,
                                                                           int j,
                                                                           int s,
                                                                           int e)
        Calculate the direction from the area [i, j) to the area [s, e).
        The direction will be the direction to head from the first area to the second area.
        For example: if A is inside B then the direction from A to B will be PARENT.
        Parameters:
        i - the first index of the first area.
        j - one past the last index of the first area.
        s - the first index of the second area.
        e - one past the last index of the second area.
        Returns:
        the direction from the first area given to the second area given.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if i is not in the range [0, j] or if s is not in the range [0, e].
        Since:
        0.2.0 ~2021.05.15
